    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p><strong>Cut</strong> the broccoli florets and the stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;into bite-size pieces</p> <p><strong>Add</strong> them to&nbsp;a baking tray, drizzle with 1-2 tbsp vegetable oil and season with salt and pepper, then put them in the oven&nbsp;for 10 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, boil a kettle&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Bash</strong> the lemongrass&nbsp;with a rolling pin, cut it <span class=\"text-danger\">[them]</span>&nbsp;down the middle lengthways, remove the tough outer layers (keep them for later!) and chop the softer inner stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;finely</p> <p><strong>Peel</strong> and chop the garlic and the ginger coarsely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong>&nbsp;the rice, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water and the outer lemongrass layers to a pot (with a lid) and bring it to the boil over a high heat</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, blitz the ginger, garlic, lemongrass stems and chilli (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a blender to form a rough paste (alternatively, chop very finely)</p> <p><strong>Combine</strong> the paste, pork mince, breadcrumbs, 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span>&nbsp;sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;soy sauce in a mixing bowl with a pinch of salt and pepper</p> <p><strong>Shape</strong> 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span>&nbsp;meatballs from the mixture</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Spread</strong> the sesame seeds out on a plate, roll the meatballs into the seeds to coat them evenly</p> <p><strong>Heat</strong> 1-2 tbsp vegetable oil in a large pan (preferably non-stick)&nbsp;over a high heat</p> <p><strong>Once</strong>&nbsp;hot, add the meatballs and cook for 3-4 min or until the meatballs have browned on all sides</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the browned meatballs to the broccoli tray (keep the pan for later!)</p> <p><strong>Return</strong> the tray to the oven for a further 8-10 min or until the meatballs have cooked through</p> <p><strong>Check</strong> the rice is cooked, and once done, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, return the pan to a medium heat, add the honey, 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[220ml]</span>&nbsp;water and the remaining soy sauce</p> <p><strong>Bring</strong> to the boil, whisk to combine and boil until reduced to a runny glaze</p> <p><strong>Tip:</strong>&nbsp;remove the pan from the heat occasionally to prevent it from over-reducing</p> <p><strong>Once</strong> done, remove from the heat</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-sesame-and-lemongrass-meatballs/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove</strong> the lemongrass layers from the cooked rice and fluff with a fork</p> <p><strong>Serve </strong>the meatballs over the rice with the broccoli to the side</p> <p><strong>Drizzle</strong> the glaze over the meatballs&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Enjoy!</strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
